<emphasis id="B9445463CE38FFCCFF54F419DB05047E" bold="true" box="[197,376,1607,1633]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="130B94F4CE38FFCCFE18F416DB91047D" box="[393,492,1608,1634]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 12" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1473,1497]" captionTargetBox="[259,1338,159,1453]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[242,1354,149,1467]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 12. Male genitalia of Ephysteris spp. 7, E. promptella (Staudinger) (slide no. L 05198); 8, E. subovata (Povolný) (slide no. L 06032); 9, E. montana sp. nov. (holotype, slide no. L 05196); 10, E. flavida Povolný (slide no. L 05190); 11, E. wenquana sp. nov. (Paratype, slide no. L 06064); 12, E. insulella (Heinemann) (slide no. L 06128)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/181379/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
Figs. 
<number id="3DF89A56CE38FFCCFE5DF416DB91047D" box="[460,492,1608,1634]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="10.16">10</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="130B94F4CE38FFCCFE68F416D867047D" box="[505,538,1608,1634]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 18" captionStartId="7.[151,269,810,834]" captionTargetBox="[277,1312,195,787]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[265,1322,173,800]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 18. Male segment VIII of Ephysteris spp. 13, E. promptella (Staudinger); 14, E. subovata (Povolný); 15, E. montana sp. n.; 16, E. flavida Povolný; 17, E. wenquana sp. n.; 18, E. insulella (Heinemann)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/181380/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">16</figureCitation>
). Posterior margin of sternite VIII with deep triangular incision. Uncus subtriangular, evenly narrowed apically, apex rounded. Gnathos relatively broad, sickle-shaped, with broadened apex. Tegumen narrow. Valva at most level with base of gnathos, evenly curved inwards, slender, of equal width, apex distinctly pointed; sacculus narrow, slightly exceeding half length of valva; paired process on posterior margin of vinculum short, subtriangular, rounded apically, medial incision deep, triangular. Saccus basally broad, triangular, distal portion very slender. Phallus about as long as tegumen, basal quarter rounded, slightly inflated, distal portion relatively slender, straight, evenly tapered with small subapical teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8F8871CE38FFC3FF54F501D9AD031D" blockId="7.[151,1436,1167,2034]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1437,152,778]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="53" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="B9445463CE38FFCCFF54F501DBE90566" bold="true" box="[197,404,1887,1913]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="130B94F4CE38FFCCFE35F53EDB800565" box="[420,509,1888,1914]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 24" captionStartId="9.[151,269,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[293,1333,212,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[224,1358,194,1895]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 24. Female genitalia of Ephysteris spp. 19, E. promptella (Staudinger) (slide no. L 06106); 20, E. subovata (Povolný) (slide no. L 06033); 21, E. montana sp. nov. (holotype, slide no. L 05197); 22, E. flavida Povolný (slide no. L 05184); 23, E. wenquana sp. nov. (paratype, slide no. L 06086); 24, E. insulella (Heinemann) (slide no. L 05194)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/181381/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF89A56CE38FFCCFE4DF53EDB800565" box="[476,509,1888,1914]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
). Apophyses anteriores straight, short. Segment VIII trapezoid, twice length of apophyses anteriores, posterior margin weakly curved anteriorly, with moderately broad suboval membranous zone between subgenital plates, which distinctly narrowed and prolonged anteromedially around ostium bursae, ostial zone covered with minute spines. Ductus bursae slender, evenly broadened near corpus bursae; antrum slightly longer than apophyses anteriores. Corpus bursae large, broadened proximally; signum a subtriangular plate, about as long as broad, with distinctly prolonged, narrow and pointed basal corners, medial process narrow, its proximal part shorter than basal corners of signum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8F8871CE37FFC3FF54F351DEDF0365" blockId="8.[151,1437,152,778]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="B9445463CE37FFC3FF54F351DB420336" bold="true" box="[197,319,271,297]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">Variation.</emphasis>
All examined specimens show slight variation in the extent of yellowish patches on forewing; the sacculus varies slightly in width; the vinculum lobes may be triangular, pointed apically, or rounded; the length of apophyses anteriores varies from half to two-thirds the length of segment VIII.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32ADBFACE37FFC3FF54F3D9DF1A03BD" box="[197,1383,391,418]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8B8F8871CE37FFC3FF54F3D9DF1A03BD" blockId="8.[151,1437,152,778]" box="[197,1383,391,418]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="B9445463CE37FFC3FF54F3D9DB5703BE" bold="true" box="[197,298,391,417]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">Biology.</emphasis>
Host plant unknown. In 
<collectingCountry id="F327C8E1CE37FFC3FDDCF3D6D8EE03BD" box="[589,659,392,418]" name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">China</collectingCountry>
adults fly in August, up to 
<quantity id="4CC82594CE37FFC3FC45F3D6DE5003BD" box="[980,1069,392,418]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" unit="m" value="1200.0">1200 m</quantity>
on northwestern altiplano.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32ADBFACE37FFC3FF54F3F1DB8803ED" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B8F8871CE37FFC3FF54F3F1DB8803ED" blockId="8.[151,1437,152,778]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="B9445463CE37FFC3FF54F3F1DB1503D6" bold="true" box="[197,360,431,457]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">Distribution:</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F327C8E1CE37FFC3FEE3F3EEDBD903D5" box="[370,420,432,458]" name="Iran" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">Iran</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F327C8E1CE37FFC3FE23F3EED85903D5" box="[434,548,432,458]" name="Mongolia" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
(Bajanchongor aimak, South Gobi aimak). In 
<collectingCountry id="F327C8E1CE37FFC3FBC2F3EEDEE403D5" box="[1107,1177,432,458]" name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">China</collectingCountry>
it was recorded from Inner 
<collectingCountry id="F327C8E1CE37FFC3FF4DF386DB3303ED" box="[220,334,472,498]" name="Mongolia" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
and Xinjiang.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32ADBFACE37FFC3FF54F3A1DA950115" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8F8871CE37FFC3FF54F3A1DA950115" blockId="8.[151,1437,152,778]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="B9445463CE37FFC3FF54F3A1DB430006" bold="true" box="[197,318,511,537]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C30F3F2CE37FFC3FED6F05ED88A0006" box="[327,759,512,537]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Ephysteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavida" subGenus="Microcraspedus">
<emphasis id="B9445463CE37FFC3FED6F05ED88A0006" box="[327,759,512,537]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">Ephysteris (Microcraspedus) flavida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recognizable externally by the yellowish-white forewing with dark costal margin, but may occasionally be confused with yellowish-coloured 
<taxonomicName id="4C30F3F2CE37FFC3FB0FF076DAB60075" authority="Povolny" authorityName="Povolny" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Ephysteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosa" subGenus="Microcraspedus">
<emphasis id="B9445463CE37FFC3FB0FF076DF23005E" box="[1182,1374,552,577]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">E. (M.) speciosa</emphasis>
Povolný
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C30F3F2CE37FFC3FE97F00ED80F0075" authority="Povolny. The" authorityName="Povolny. The" box="[262,626,592,618]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Ephysteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chretieni" subGenus="Microcraspedus">
<emphasis id="B9445463CE37FFC3FE97F00EDBB70076" box="[262,458,592,617]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">E. (M.) chretieni</emphasis>
Povolný. The
</taxonomicName>
male genitalia are characterized by the slender, evenly curved valva not expanded apically, the short, paired process on the posterior margin of the vinculum, and the slender distal portion of the phallus. The female genitalia resemble particularly those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C30F3F2CE37FFC3FB99F0FEDEAA00A6" box="[1032,1239,672,697]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Ephysteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="treskensis" subGenus="Microcraspedus">
<emphasis id="B9445463CE37FFC3FB99F0FEDEAA00A6" box="[1032,1239,672,697]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">E. (M.) treskensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C30F3F2CE37FFC3FB76F0FEDAC600FE" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Ephysteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispanica" subGenus="Microcraspedus">
<emphasis id="B9445463CE37FFC3FB76F0FEDAC600FE" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">E. (M.) hispanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C30F3F2CE37FFC3FF6FF096DB9F00FE" box="[254,482,712,737]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Ephysteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diminutella" subGenus="Microcraspedus">
<emphasis id="B9445463CE37FFC3FF6FF096DB9F00FE" box="[254,482,712,737]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">E. (M.) diminutella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differ in the broader, subtriangular signum and the ostial zone with minute spines.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
